definition: conclusive in a process or progression, a computer network consisting of a worldwide network of computer networks that use the TCP/IP network protocols to facilitate data transmission and exchange, catch with a net
details:
adjective
- conclusive in a process or progression
= synonyms: last
- remaining after all deductions
= example: remaining after all deductions
= synonyms: nett
noun
- a computer network consisting of a worldwide network of computer networks that use the TCP/IP network protocols to facilitate data transmission and exchange
= synonyms: internet, cyberspace
- an open fabric of string or rope or wire woven together at regular intervals
= synonyms: mesh
- a trap made of netting to catch fish or birds or insects
- game equipment consisting of a strip of netting dividing the playing area in tennis or badminton
- a goal lined with netting (as in soccer or hockey)
- the excess of revenues over outlays in a given period of time (including depreciation and other non-cash expenses)
= synonyms: profit, net income, net profit, lucre, profits, earnings
verb
- catch with a net
= example: catch with a net
= synonyms: nett
- construct or form a web, as if by weaving
= synonyms: web
- make as a net profit
= synonyms: sack
- yield as a net profit
= example: yield as a net profit
= synonyms: clear
